## AWS Policy Configuration

The JSON policy example below was generated using the AWS Policy Generator, which helps ensure that the policy conforms to AWS standards and best practices. This policy grants extensive permissions (`s3:*`) to a specific AWS IAM user for operations on a designated S3 bucket. This is a redacted version for demonstration purposes, with placeholders used to protect sensitive information.

```json
{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Id": "PolicyExample",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Sid": "StmtExample",
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Principal": {
                "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::[AWS Account ID]:user/[User Name]"
            },
            "Action": "s3:*",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::[Bucket Name]"
        }
    ]
}
